records.addlTxt:
03:20 PM Defendant Meghan A McWilliams in court with attorney Nicole Marie Ostrowski.  Charles Patrick Hoffmann appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases called for plea and sentencing.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy. 

In case 22CM423: 
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.

In case 22CM424:
  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
  Count 2 is Dismissed and read in.
  Count 3 is Dismissed by Operation of law.

Counts in Cases 22CM440 & 22TR1659 are Dismissed and read in.

State and Defense make sentencing recommendations. 
Defendant makes statement to the Court. 

In case 22CM423: 
Court orders the following:
SENTENCE WITHHELD. Consecutive to 22CM424.

Term of Probation: 2 YEARS; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Compliance with OWI Treatment Court;
*Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate;

CONDITION TIME: 60 DAYS, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  Concurrent to 22CM424.

COSTS:  $1,544
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
To be paid as a Condition of Probation. All Fees/Fines/Surcharges to be converted to civil judgment for non-payment.

